    "statement": "For $n\\ge 2$ let $B_n$ be the $n \\times n$ $0\\text{–}1$ matrix with\n\\[\n(B_n)_{ij} = \\begin{cases} 1, & |i-j|\\le 1,\\\\ 0, & |i-j|\\ge 2,\\end{cases}\n\\]\ni.e. ones on the main diagonal and on the two adjacent diagonals, zeros elsewhere. Find $\\operatorname{rank} B_n$ as a function of $n$.",
    "answer": "\\operatorname{rank} B_n = \\begin{cases} n-1, & n\\equiv 2 \\pmod 3,\\\\ n, & n\\not\\equiv 2 \\pmod 3.\\end{cases}\\qquad\\bigl(\\det B_n=1,0,-1,-1,0,1\\text{ for }n=1,2,3,4,5,6,\\text{ then period }6\\bigr)",
