          "The eigenvalues of $T$ are classically $2\\cos\\!\\frac{k\\pi}{n+1}$, $k=1,\\dots,n$. Hence the eigenvalues of $B_n$ are $1+2\\cos\\!\\frac{k\\pi}{n+1}.$",
          "$\\operatorname{rank} B_n=n-\\#\\{k:\\,1+2\\cos\\frac{k\\pi}{n+1}=0\\}.$ The condition $\\cos\\frac{k\\pi}{n+1}=-\\tfrac12$ means $\\frac{k\\pi}{n+1}=\\frac{2\\pi}{3}$, i.e. $3k=2(n+1).$",
          "This has an integer solution $k$ with $1\\le k\\le n$ **iff** $3\\mid(n+1)$, i.e. $n\\equiv 2\\pmod 3$, and then exactly one $k$ (namely $k=\\tfrac{2(n+1)}{3}$) qualifies. So the rank is $n-1$ when $n\\equiv2\\pmod3$ and $n$ otherwise. $\\boxed{}$"
