          "It is also sufficient: writing $L=D^{\\mathsf T}D$, solving $Lx=b$ amounts to finding $y=Dx$ (an edge vector) with $D^{\\mathsf T}y=b$ and $y\\in\\operatorname{Row}(D)$. The condition $\\mathbf 1^{\\mathsf T}b=0$ places $b$ in $\\operatorname{Col}(D^{\\mathsf T})=\\operatorname{Row}(D)^{\\mathsf T}$, after which $x$ is recovered from $y$ by telescoping (discrete summation) $x_i=x_1+\\sum_{e<i}y_e$, the constant $x_1$ being free.",
