          "Then $AB$ is just the top-left $r\\times n$ slab of $B$ (rows $1$–$r$), padded with zero rows. So $\\operatorname{rank}(AB)=\\operatorname{rank}(\\text{first }r\\text{ rows of }B).$",
          "The first $r$ rows of a rank-$s$ matrix $B$ can have any rank $k$ with $k\\le\\min(r,s)$ and $k\\ge s-(n-r)=r+s-n$ (the last $n-r$ rows can carry at most $n-r$ independent directions, so the top must supply at least $s-(n-r)$).",
