    "statement": "Let $M=\\begin{pmatrix} A & B \\\\ C & D \\end{pmatrix}$ be invertible with $A$ ($n\\times n$) invertible, and write the Schur complement $S=D-CA^{-1}B$ ($m\\times m$).\n(a) Prove $S$ is invertible and that the bottom-right $m\\times m$ block of $M^{-1}$ equals $S^{-1}$.\n(b) Apply this to find the $(n+1,n+1)$ entry of the inverse of $\\begin{pmatrix} I_n+J_n & \\mathbf 1 \\\\ \\mathbf 1^{\\mathsf T} & 2 \\end{pmatrix}$, where $J_n$ is all-ones and $\\mathbf 1=(1,\\dots,1)^{\\mathsf T}$.",
