          "Since $A,B$ are real, complex conjugation gives $\\overline{A+iB}=A-iB$, hence $\\det(A-iB)=\\det\\overline{(A+iB)}=\\overline{\\det(A+iB)}$. Therefore $\\det M=\\det(A+iB)\\,\\overline{\\det(A+iB)}=\\big|\\det(A+iB)\\big|^2\\ge0$.",
