          "Consequently $\\operatorname{tr}\\bigl((PQ)^{k}\\bigr)=\\operatorname{tr}\\bigl(T^{k}\\bigr)=\\sum_{i}\\cos^{2k}\\theta_{i}\\ge 0$, re-deriving (a) and the ladder. For (c): with $p=2,\\ q=1$ we have $m=\\min(p,q)=1$, a single principal angle between the plane $z=0$ and the line $\\mathbb{R}w$. Then $\\cos^{2}\\theta=\\|Pw\\|^{2}=\\tfrac59$, so $\\operatorname{tr}(PQ)=\\tfrac59\\in[0,1]=[0,\\min(2,1)]$ and $\\operatorname{tr}\\bigl((PQ)^{2}\\bigr)=\\cos^{4}\\theta=\\tfrac{25}{81}$. The bound $0\\le\\tfrac59\\le 1$ is satisfied, and the non-integer value $\\tfrac59$ certifies $PQ$ is not a projection. $\\boxed{\\operatorname{tr}(PQ)=\\tfrac59,\\ \\operatorname{tr}((PQ)^{2})=\\tfrac{25}{81}}$"
