    "statement": "Fix an integer $n\\ge 2$ and build the directed graph $G_n$ on the vertex set $\\mathbb{Z}_n=\\{0,1,\\dots,n-1\\}$ by drawing an edge $i\\to j$ exactly when the step $j-i$ is a unit modulo $n$, i.e. $\\gcd(j-i,\\,n)=1$. Let $A\\in M_n(\\mathbb{Z})$ be its $0/1$ adjacency matrix, so $A_{ij}=1$ iff $\\gcd(j-i,n)=1$. Equivalently, with $P$ the cyclic-shift permutation matrix ($P_{i,\\,i+1}=1$ indices mod $n$),\n\\[\nA=\\sum_{\\substack{a=1\\\\ \\gcd(a,n)=1}}^{n}P^{\\,a},\n\\]\na $0/1$ circulant.\\par (a) Show that the eigenvalues of $A$ are precisely the Ramanujan sums $c_n(j)=\\displaystyle\\sum_{\\gcd(a,n)=1}e^{2\\pi i a j/n}$ for $j=0,1,\\dots,n-1$, so the walk-counting matrix $A$ has a purely number-theoretic spectrum.\n\\par (b) Let $W_2(n)$ be the total number of closed walks of length $2$ in $G_n$ (ordered: a vertex $i$, then $i\\to i+a\\to i+a+b=i$ with $a,b$ units). Prove that\n\\[\nW_2(n)=\\operatorname{tr}\\!\\bigl(A^{2}\\bigr)=\\sum_{j=0}^{n-1}c_n(j)^{2}=n\\,\\varphi(n),\n\\]\nwhere $\\varphi$ is Euler's totient. Evaluate $W_2(12)$.",
