    "statement": "For an integer $n\\ge 1$, the fan graph $F_n$ is built from a path $P_n$ on vertices $1,2,\\dots,n$ (with edges $\\{i,i+1\\}$ for $1\\le i\\le n-1$) by adjoining one extra hub vertex $0$ joined to every path vertex by a spoke $\\{0,i\\}$, $1\\le i\\le n$. Thus $F_n$ has $n+1$ vertices and $2n-1$ edges.\\par (a) Using the Matrix-Tree theorem, show that the number $\\tau(F_n)$ of spanning trees of $F_n$ equals the determinant of an $n\\times n$ symmetric tridiagonal matrix $D_n$ whose interior diagonal entries are $3$, whose two outermost diagonal entries are $2$, and whose off-diagonal entries are $-1$:\n\\[\nD_n=\\begin{pmatrix} 2 & -1 & & & \\\\ -1 & 3 & -1 & & \\\\ & -1 & 3 & \\ddots & \\\\ & & \\ddots & \\ddots & -1 \\\\ & & & -1 & 2 \\end{pmatrix}.\n\\]\n\\par (b) Prove that for $n\\ge 3$ the value $d_n:=\\det D_n$ obeys the continuant recursion $d_n=3d_{n-1}-d_{n-2}$, with $d_1=1,\\ d_2=3$, and deduce the closed form. Identify $\\tau(F_n)$ as a single term of the Fibonacci sequence $F_1=F_2=1,\\ F_{m}=F_{m-1}+F_{m-2}$.State which Fibonacci number $\\tau(F_n)$ is, in closed form valid for all $n\\ge 1$.",
