          "To connect this to the determinant, observe that the all-threes continuant is itself a transfer-matrix power: $C_k$'s determinant satisfies $\\begin{pmatrix}c_k\\\\c_{k-1}\\end{pmatrix}=\\begin{pmatrix}3&-1\\\\1&0\\end{pmatrix}\\begin{pmatrix}c_{k-1}\\\\c_{k-2}\\end{pmatrix}$, and $\\begin{pmatrix}3&-1\\\\1&0\\end{pmatrix}=Q^{2}\\!\\cdot\\!\\det$-conjugate, with eigenvalues $\\varphi^{2},\\varphi^{-2}$; iterating from $(c_1,c_0)=(3,1)$ yields $c_k=F_{2k+2}$.",
