          "The eigenvalues of $S$ are exactly the $n$-th roots of unity $w^k$, so the eigenvalues of $C_n(x)=p(S)$ are $p(w^k)=\\sum_{j}(xw^k)^j=\\dfrac{x^n-1}{xw^k-1}$ (and $=n$ when $xw^k=1$), recovering the spectrum of method 1.",
