    "remark": "**Insight.** The orthogonal $Q$ exploits the $\\mathbb Z/2$ symmetry $M\\!\\leftrightarrow\\!\\begin{pmatrix}0&I\\\\I&0\\end{pmatrix}M\\begin{pmatrix}0&I\\\\I&0\\end{pmatrix}$; any matrix commuting with an involution splits into its $\\pm1$-eigenspaces. The inequality is the determinant form of *Minkowski's determinant inequality* / concavity of $\\log\\det$, the matrix analogue of AM–GM, and it generalises: for any PSD $X_1,\\dots,X_m$, $\\det\\!\\big(\\tfrac1m\\sum X_i\\big)\\ge\\big(\\prod\\det X_i\\big)^{1/m}$."
