    "statement": "Fix an odd integer $n\\ge 3$ and let $S$ be the $n\\times n$ cyclic shift, $S\\,e_i=e_{i+1}$ (indices mod $n$). The adjacency matrix of the cycle $C_n$ is the real symmetric circulant\n\\[\nA=S+S^{\\mathsf T},\\qquad A_{ij}=\\begin{cases}1,&i-j\\equiv\\pm 1\\ (\\mathrm{mod}\\ n),\\\\0,&\\text{otherwise.}\\end{cases}\n\\]\nLet $T_n$ denote the degree-$n$ Chebyshev polynomial of the first kind ($T_n(\\cos\\theta)=\\cos n\\theta$). Carry out the following capstone.\n\n(a) Prove the spectral identity\n\\[\n\\det(xI-A)=2\\bigl(T_n(x/2)-1\\bigr).\n\\]\n\n(b) A closed walk of length $n$ on $C_n$ is a sequence $v_0,v_1,\\dots,v_n$ of vertices with $v_0=v_n$ and each consecutive pair adjacent. Let $W_n$ be the total number of closed walks of length $n$ (summed over all $n$ possible starting vertices). Using part (a), evaluate $W_n$ in closed form, and identify exactly which walks are counted.\n\n(c) Show that the $n-1$ eigenvalues of $A$ other than the top one obey an isoperimetric-type estimate forcing $n\\ge 3$, with equality precisely for the triangle, and explain what makes it tight there.\n\nReport the value of $W_n$ as your headline answer.",
