          "Form the two graph Laplacians. $A+B=\\begin{pmatrix}3&-1&-1\\\\-1&3&-1\\\\-1&-1&3\\end{pmatrix}=I+L(K_3)$ is the grounded Laplacian of the triangle with all three signs erased plus the unit ground leaks; this is exactly the reduced Laplacian of the wheel $W_3=K_4$ (triangle $+$ ground hub). By the Matrix-Tree theorem $\\det(A+B)=\\tau(K_4)=4^{4-2}=16$.",
          "$A-B=\\begin{pmatrix}3&1&-1\\\\1&3&-1\\\\-1&-1&3\\end{pmatrix}$ is the grounded Laplacian of the flipped quotient, where the negative edge has been switched to the antivoltage sheet; expanding, $\\det(A-B)=3(9-1)-1(3-1)-1(-1+3)=24-2-2=20$. (Equivalently it counts the weighted spanning trees of the second quotient network.)",
