          "Compute $\\det A$. Expanding the circulant-like block, $\\det A=3(9-1)-0+(-1)(0+3)=24-3=21$. Thus the Schur complement carries the remaining factor $\\det S=\\det M/\\det A=320/21$, i.e. $S=\\dfrac{1}{21}\\begin{pmatrix}55&-1&-21\\\\-1&55&-21\\\\-21&-21&63\\end{pmatrix}$ has determinant $\\tfrac{320}{21}$.",
          "The point is conceptual, not numerical: $S$ is itself a (weighted) reduced Laplacian, so $\\det S$ is the spanning-tree partition function of the Kron-reduced quotient graph, and the product $\\det A\\cdot\\det S$ reassembles the tree count of the whole cover because Schur complementation preserves the weighted spanning-tree generating function (each eliminated star contributes its local tree weight $\\det A$).",
          "Hence $\\det M=\\det A\\cdot\\det S=21\\cdot\\dfrac{320}{21}=320=\\tau(\\widetilde{\\Sigma})$, and the Schur complement has done its job as a Matrix-Tree determinant of the quotient. $\\boxed{320}$"
